# Brand Guidelines for Web Application Design

## Typography System

### Primary Typeface
- **Travelia**: Dynamic sans serif family for main elements
  - **Travelia Bold**: Headers (200pt), secondary logo
  - **Travelia Black**: Business cards, minimal copy placements
  - **Travelia Medium**: Subheaders (50pt, 25% of header size)

### Body Copy Typeface
- **Azeret Mono Light**: Primary body copy (30pt, 42pt line spacing - 40% more than font size)
- **Azeret Mono Regular**: Body copy categories, section titles, display-oriented text

### Supporting Typefaces
- **Doto Semi-Bold**: Subject lines, footers, page numbers (30pt)
  - Can be used for design elements like quotation marks
  - Never use for headlines, subheaders, or body copy
- **BN Hightide with glyphs**: Display applications, titles only
  - Embrace alternate glyphs (especially for 'a' and 'n')
  - Use only for title pages in decks, never for formal applications

### Type Hierarchy
- **Headers**: Travelia Bold (100pt)
- **Sub-headers**: Travelia Medium (50pt)
- **Body copy categories**: Azeret Mono Regular (30pt)
- **Body copy**: Azeret Mono Light (30pt)
- **Subject lines & page numbers**: Doto Semi-Bold (30pt)

## Logo Guidelines
- The word "enlighten" must only use **Travelia Bold**
- Never use Azeret Mono, Doto, or BN Hightide to represent the brand in isolation
- Never spell "enlighten" in display settings with any typeface other than Travelia Bold

## Color Palette

### Primary Colors
- **Black**: #262628 (RGB: 38, 38, 40)
- **Purple**: #9C54AD (RGB: 156, 84, 173)
- **Red**: #EB2726 (RGB: 235, 39, 38)
- **Blue**: #3C76A9 (RGB: 60, 118, 169)
- **Green**: #6DC19C (RGB: 109, 193, 156)
- **Orange**: #F69757 (RGB: 246, 151, 87)
- **Yellow**: #FFCF4F (RGB: 255, 207, 79)
- **Light Gray**: #E9EDF3 (RGB: 233, 237, 243)

### Color Usage
- Prioritize legibility
- Avoid stacking light and dark colors that reduce readability
- Use black and white for type unless alternate color is needed for contrast
- Brand colors can be used as backgrounds with white or black text for contrast

## Brand Voice
- **Positioning**: Data-Driven. Results-Focused. AI-Powered.
- **Messaging Tone**: Professional, knowledgeable, innovative

## Design Principles
- Maintain clean, intentional lines
- Embrace modern, digital-first aesthetic
- Create clear visual hierarchy using type system
- Ensure high legibility for all text
- Use pixelated elements (via Doto) sparingly to nod to computing foundations

## Web Application Specific Guidelines
- **Navigation**: Travelia Medium for main navigation items
- **Buttons**: Travelia Bold on solid brand colors with appropriate contrast
- **Headers**: Travelia Bold in black (or white on dark backgrounds)
- **Body text**: Azeret Mono Light for readability
- **UI elements** (tabs, form labels): Azeret Mono Regular
- **Footers, small UI elements**: Doto Semi-Bold
- **Background colors**: Primarily white with brand colors as accents
- **Call to action elements**: Use brand colors (blue, purple, red) for emphasis